(755, 'Conseillers Commerciaux Experts en Assurance Santé ou Auto : Salaire jusqu’à 30 000 dhs (Courtier Français) Conseillers Commerciaux Experts en Assurance Santé ou Auto : Salaire jusqu’à 30 000 dhs (Courtier Français)', 'https://www.rekrute.com/fr/offre-emploi-qa-engineer-recrutement-axa-group-operations-maroc-rabat-166508.html', 'rekrute.com', '25/11/2024', '25/01/2025', 'Tour Végétale JASMIN | 1, rue des Plateformes - Lot N°123 20036 Casablanca', '/fr/axa-group-operations-maroc-emploi-recrutement-322155.html', 'AXA Group Operations Maroc', 'Éducation et formation', 'Consultant en informatique', '1 poste(s) sur Casablanca et région - Maroc', 'Casablanca', 'Centres d\'appels', 'Métiers des centres d\'appels', 'CDI', 'Bac +5', 'Informatique / Electronique - Secteur Informatique', 'Debutant', 'JOB PURPOSE: As a Senior QA Engineer, you will join the IAAS Product Quality Assurance Team. The role of the QA team is to continuously control/improve the quality of the Cloud IAAS product (MPI). As such, it is a central team that works across the board, managing the testing activities, environments, measurement, best practices and providing support for the users and the component teams. Involved from the design of developments to the production, the team’s goal is to achieve the expected level of quality of service while allowing the enrichment of the offer to meet the customer’s needs. A Senior QA Engineer works closely with: • The QA lead to execute the test strategy, report on testing activities & defect status • The product owner to find/report gaps in the business logic and ensure that the software is creating value for the customer • The developers (AZURE and AWS Competency Centers) for the BAU acceptance testing and the bugs fixing • The entity experts for support purposes, demos, and documentation This position will also review product documentation and track quality assurance metrics while monitoring all stages of product development to identify and resolve system defects & meet quality standards. POSITION & MISSIONS: The objective of Tech Lead is to make sure that delivered product is matching the specifications, requirements as well as the group standards (security, audit...) by applying the principles and best practices of software quality assurance. In this role you will: • Gateway between QA and CC team (Both CSP), keep the same approach for QA Azure and QA AWS on the tool, type of tests, name etc. • Review requirements, specifications, and technical design documentation in order to prioritize, estimate and organize the backlog • Contribute to define the overall product test automation strategy. • Upgrade automated architecture test to cover new features. • Overseeing the creation of detailed, comprehensive, and well-structured test cases for automation testing. • Finops activities for the QA team (adding Finops new features) • Develop and maintain automated test scripts for functional regression coverage. • Support the QA automation engineers on automated tests on a technical level. • Ensure that all assigned project deliverables meet the quality objectives in functionality, usability, integration, regression, performance, stability, security, and compliance. Overseeing automation documentation is up to date.', 'Recherche de nouveauté Ambition Besoin de réflexion Besoin d\'autonomie Implication au travail', '', 'Recherche de nouveauté Ambition Besoin de réflexion Besoin d\'autonomie Implication au travail', '', 'Anglais', 7800, 'Non'),
